text: (bright music)
- If I had to describe my days,

I would say that they are
going to be ambiguous.
They're exciting. No day is the same.

What originally attracted
me to AWS was the culture
and the people.

I am currently a member of
several of our affinity groups.

So being a member of the
affinity groups is great
for networking, career development,

and also gives you a chance
to mentor your peers.

My proudest moment at AWS is
helping to onboard my peers.
So I've been here for two years.

I was one of the first
people hired on my team,

and knowing that I'm
helping my peers uplevel
has been something that I'm most proud of.

I would say my favorite
leadership principle
is customer obsession.
And I know everyone says that,
but truly we are customer obsessed
and we work backwards from our customers.
